.SH "BASIC USAGE"
To generate a roff man page from the included \fBronn\.5\.ronn\fR file and open it with man(1):
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

$ ronn man/ronn\.5\.ronn
roff: man/ronn\.5
html: man/ronn\.5\.html

# view the generated roff manpage with man(1):
$ man man/ronn\.5

# view the generated HTML manpage
$ open man/ronn\.5\.html
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
To generate only a standalone HTML version of the manpage:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

$ ronn \-\-html man/markdown\.5\.ronn
html: man/markdown\.5\.html
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
To build roff versions of all ronn files in a directory:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

$ ronn \-\-roff man/*\.ronn
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
If you just want to view a ronn file as if it were a man page without building intermediate files:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

$ ronn \-m man/markdown\.5\.ronn
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
